olive oil
½ Lemon
2 Potato
1 Apple
1 packet Parsley
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Smooth Dory Fillets
½ packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)

• Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil over high heat.
• Zest lemon to get a generous pinch, then slice into wedges. Peel potato, then cut into large chunks. Thinly slice apple. Finely chop parsley.
• Discard any liquid from white fish fillet packaging. Slice fish in half crossways to get 1 piece per person.

• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
• Drain, then transfer potato to a large bowl. Season to taste, cover to keep warm and set aside.
• Meanwhile, add apple and mixed salad leaves to a medium bowl. Set aside.
• In a second medium bowl, combine garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add fish and turn to coat. Set aside.

• While the potato is cooking, combine panko breadcrumbs (see ingredients) and a drizzle of olive oil in a small bowl.
• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook panko mixture, stirring, until golden brown,
3-4 minutes.
• Add lemon zest and parsley and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Return to the small bowl and season to taste.

• Set your air fryer to 200°C
• Place dory fillet into the air fryer basket and cook until just cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: No air fryer? Wipe out and return pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook until just cooked through, 5-6 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.
TIP: White fish is cooked through when the centre turns from translucent to white.

• Meanwhile, return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon,
until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Transfer bacon to the bowl with potatoes. Add dill & parsley mayonnaise, a squeeze of lemon juice, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt
and pepper. Toss to coat.

• Add a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil to the apple salad and toss to coat.
• Slice garlicky fish.
• Divide creamy bacon potato salad, apple salad and fish between plates. Top fish with parsley crumb.
• Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!